                  wireless network (e.g., WiFi, 4G/5G) with the augmented
                  ability to sense the surrounding human and environment, and
                  evolve wireless communication networks into intelligent
                  communication and sensing network (e.g., 6G). In this paper,
                  based on our experience on CSI-based wireless sensing with
                  WiFi/4G/5G signals, we intend to identify ten major practical
                  and theoretical problems that hinder real deployment of ISAC
                  applications, and provide possible solutions to those critical
                  challenges. Hopefully, this work will inspire further research
                  to evolve existing WiFi/4G/5G networks into next-generation
                  intelligent wireless network (i.e., 6G).},
